The paper discusses the convergence rates of gradient descent on rectifier convnets, which are widely used in deep learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also introduces gated games, which is an extension of convex games, indicating a possible connection to cs.GT (Game Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the analysis of conditional computation in neural nets, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
